name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: Business identifiers assigned to this adverse event by the performer or other systems which remain constant as the resource is updated and propagates from server to server.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Business identifiers assigned to this adverse event by the performer or other systems which remain constant as the resource is updated and propagates from server to server.

name: $actuality
desc: Returns: Whether the event actually happened, or just had the potential to. Note that this is independent of whether anyone was affected or harmed or how severely.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Whether the event actually happened, or just had the potential to. Note that this is independent of whether anyone was affected or harmed or how severely.

name: $category
desc: Returns: The overall type of event, intended for search and filtering purposes.

name: $addcategory
desc: The overall type of event, intended for search and filtering purposes.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The overall type of event, intended for search and filtering purposes.

name: $event
desc: Returns: This element defines the specific type of event that occurred or that was prevented from occurring.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: This element defines the specific type of event that occurred or that was prevented from occurring.

name: $subject
desc: Returns: This subject or group impacted by the event.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: This subject or group impacted by the event.

name: $encounter
desc: Returns: The Encounter during which AdverseEvent was created or to which the creation of this record is tightly associated.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The Encounter during which AdverseEvent was created or to which the creation of this record is tightly associated.

name: $date
desc: Returns: The date (and perhaps time) when the adverse event occurred.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date (and perhaps time) when the adverse event occurred.

name: $detected
desc: Returns: Estimated or actual date the AdverseEvent began, in the opinion of the reporter.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Estimated or actual date the AdverseEvent began, in the opinion of the reporter.

name: $recordedDate
desc: Returns: The date on which the existence of the AdverseEvent was first recorded.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date on which the existence of the AdverseEvent was first recorded.

name: $resultingCondition
desc: Returns: Includes information about the reaction that occurred as a result of exposure to a substance (for example, a drug or a chemical).

name: $addresultingCondition
desc: Includes information about the reaction that occurred as a result of exposure to a substance (for example, a drug or a chemical).

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Includes information about the reaction that occurred as a result of exposure to a substance (for example, a drug or a chemical).

name: $location
desc: Returns: The information about where the adverse event occurred.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The information about where the adverse event occurred.

name: $seriousness
desc: Returns: Assessment whether this event was of real importance.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Assessment whether this event was of real importance.

name: $severity
desc: Returns: Describes the severity of the adverse event, in relation to the subject. Contrast to AdverseEvent.seriousness - a severe rash might not be serious, but a mild heart problem is.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Describes the severity of the adverse event, in relation to the subject. Contrast to AdverseEvent.seriousness - a severe rash might not be serious, but a mild heart problem is.

name: $outcome
desc: Returns: Describes the type of outcome from the adverse event.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Describes the type of outcome from the adverse event.

name: $recorder
desc: Returns: Information on who recorded the adverse event.  May be the patient or a practitioner.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Information on who recorded the adverse event.  May be the patient or a practitioner.

name: $contributor
desc: Returns: Parties that may or should contribute or have contributed information to the adverse event, which can consist of one or more activities.  Such information includes information leading to the decision to perform the activity and how to perform the activity (e.g. consultant), information that the activity itself seeks to reveal (e.g. informant of clinical history), or information about what activity was performed (e.g. informant witness).

name: $addcontributor
desc: Parties that may or should contribute or have contributed information to the adverse event, which can consist of one or more activities.  Such information includes information leading to the decision to perform the activity and how to perform the activity (e.g. consultant), information that the activity itself seeks to reveal (e.g. informant of clinical history), or information about what activity was performed (e.g. informant witness).

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Parties that may or should contribute or have contributed information to the adverse event, which can consist of one or more activities.  Such information includes information leading to the decision to perform the activity and how to perform the activity

name: $suspectEntity
desc: Returns: Describes the entity that is suspected to have caused the adverse event.

name: $addsuspectEntity
desc: Describes the entity that is suspected to have caused the adverse event.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Describes the entity that is suspected to have caused the adverse event.

name: $subjectMedicalHistory
desc: Returns: AdverseEvent.subjectMedicalHistory.

name: $addsubjectMedicalHistory
desc: AdverseEvent.subjectMedicalHistory.

name: $referenceDocument
desc: Returns: AdverseEvent.referenceDocument.

name: $addreferenceDocument
desc: AdverseEvent.referenceDocument.

name: $study
desc: Returns: AdverseEvent.study.

name: $addstudy
desc: AdverseEvent.study.
